## Local Architecture

```
City root: {{ .CityRoot }}
Rig root:  {{ .RigRoot }}
Workspace: {{ .WorkDir }}
```

Key concepts:
- the city root owns shared runtime state and city-level coordination
- the rig root is the repo whose work you primarily own in this session
- the owner session is the persistent, high-context path for larger work
- optional workers handle smaller, branch-oriented tasks when you decide to use them
- beads, hook, and mail provide the durable work and handoff surfaces
